  • Populated Dimensional Tables


  1. Using SSIS Toolbox, drag Execute SQL Task into the control flow dashboard.
  2. Using SSIS Toolbox, drag the Sequence Container and inside the container add the Data Flow Task for each Dimensional Tables.


  1. Edited Executed SQL Task
  2. Click on General
  3. Write SQL Statement
  4. Click Ok



*Edited each components in each Data Flow Task.

*Followed the same step to edit each Data Flow Task for each Dimensional Tables. The SSIS package, is the same for ALL Dim tables.


  1. Click on Connection Manager
  2. Select the desired Connection Manager
  3. Select the table that is needed. Table will varies 
  4. Preview the table selected
  5. Click Columns and select All the columns that is needed


  1. Click on General, select the following as shown for all the dimensional(Lookup) Tables
  2. Click on connection, select the connection manager and table that is needed
  3. Click on Columns, match the look up columns and check the select name columns that is needed
